# Project Overview

**dpm-core-client** is a web application built for members and organizers of an intercollegiate IT club.  
The project is developed using **Next.js** and **TypeScript**, with modern libraries for UI, data fetching, and styling.

---
## 🔧 Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js + TypeScript  
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS  
- **UI Library**: [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/)  
- **Data Fetching**: react-query, axios  
- **Authentication**: [better-auth](https://www.better-auth.com/)  
- **Code Formatting**: [Biome](https://biomejs.dev/)

---

## 📁 Project Structure

- `components/` – Reusable UI components  
- `app/` – Routing configuration using Next.js App Router  
- `hooks/` – Custom React hooks for shared logic

---

## 🧑‍💻 Development Guidelines

- Use **TypeScript** for type safety and better DX.
- Enforce formatting and linting with **Biome**.
- Ensure all components are:
  - **Reusable**
  - **Responsive**
  - **Accessible**
- Style components using **Tailwind CSS**, following design tokens.
- Customize `shadcn/ui` components only when necessary and keep it consistent.

---

## 📜 Important Scripts

| Script | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `dev`  | Starts the development server |
| `build` | Builds the application for production |

---

## 🤖 AI Interaction Guidelines

- Always follow **React + TypeScript best practices** when generating code.
- Use **clear and meaningful names** for functions and variables.
- Avoid unnecessary AI-generated comments.
- Validate all user inputs and handle errors gracefully.
- Follow existing patterns and structure when adding new components or pages.

---

## 🎯 Target Users

- **Organizers** – Manage participants, announcements, and club operations  
- **Participants** – Join programs, track activities, and stay informed

